# Generated dependency files are byte-compared by the CI `deps` job (the
# `uv export` diff guard) on Linux, where uv writes LF line endings. Pin them to
# LF so the committed blob matches that output regardless of a contributor's
# core.autocrlf setting — otherwise a CRLF commit from Windows fails the guard.
requirements.txt text eol=lf
uv.lock          text eol=lf

# Committed runtime data (gold + the silver facts the deployed app reads). Mark
# binary so git never line-ending-normalizes them — a CRLF rewrite on Windows
# would corrupt the parquet/avatar payload. git auto-detects this, but pin it.
*.parquet binary
*.jpg     binary
*.jpeg    binary
*.png     binary
*.webp    binary
